SIMPLE: polyglot
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Polyglot
<hw>Pol"y*glot</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>poly`glwttos</grk> many-tongued; <grk>poly`s</grk> many +
<grk>glw^tta</grk>, <grk>glw^ssa</grk>, tongue, language: cf. F.
<ets>polyglotte</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Containing, or made up,
of, several languages; <as>as, a <ex>polyglot</ex> lexicon,
Bible</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Versed in, or speaking, many languages.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polyglot</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Polyglot
<hw>Pol"y*glot</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who speaks
several languages.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>polyglot</xex>,
or good linguist.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Howell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A book containing several versions of the same text,
or containing the same subject matter in several languages; esp., the
Scriptures in several languages.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Enriched by the publication of <qex>polyglots</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Abp. Newcome.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polyglottous</ent>⟦br⟧
